# Bytes in, bytes out. No end-of-line conversion in either direction.
#
# Git for Windows ships with core.autocrlf=true at the SYSTEM level, which rewrites LF to CRLF on
# checkout and back on commit. That silently mangles anything it wrongly guesses is text - and this
# repo is full of things it would guess wrong about: game archives, .fcb/.xbt/.dat binaries, hash
# lists, tool executables.
# core.autocrlf is per-machine, so it cannot be relied on to travel with the repo. This file can.
# `-text` disables the conversion entirely, for every file, for every clone.
* -text
reverse/ghidra/*.gzf filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
tools/JackAll/assets/ffmpeg.exe filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
